    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <dateline>Jan. 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1774.</dateline>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>one favor with a Letter from <persName ref="pe0188">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Campbell</persName> another with the prints are received with
                    thanks.</p>
                <p>I scarce know what to advise about <persName ref="pe0005">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> aulds</persName>
                    <unclear reason="illegible">compunction</unclear>. are <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0530">N<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. 9. 10 11. 12 vol.
                            II Advoc. Libr.</title>
                    </bibl> worth attention?</p>
                <p>
                    <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0105">Stukelyâ€™s Stone hinge</title>
                    </bibl>
                    is a fanciful book. <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0106">Borlases
                            Antiquities of Cornwall</title>
                    </bibl> is the best book <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> can have.</p>
                <p>I have told him to draw on me for twenty pounds in aid of his voyage.</p>
                <p>In respect to y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> earnestness ab<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> sending him books, you are very kind but he had best collect all his
                    materials &amp; then form his remarks from Books.</p>
                <p>Pray transmit to him the inclosed hints.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>I like <rs type="art" ref="ar0121">the Prints</rs> much, you favord me with.
                        They are prettily designed.</p>
                    <p>Pray inform me of the weight of an <placeName ref="pl0715">isle of
                            skie</placeName> Steer, &amp; cow the Butchers or graziers are best to
                        advise with. </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
